  "text": "Other factors involved in tissue retention include inflammatory cytokines such as transforming growth factor (TGF)-β, interleukin (IL)-33, and tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-α. TGF-β was shown to induce CD103 expression on mouse memory CD8 + T cells, and IL-33 and TNF-α were found to synergize with TGF-β [CITATION_1] .",
